content: Such a good game!
Brilliant game, I've also own the real card game as well.
Can't see the top of the screen on my android 11 phone. Would try again if fixed
Goodt
Really good game with somewhat quirky interface that took me some time to get used to. Manual has small font which is hard to read and cannot be pinched out to zoom in. I still play it all the time.
A fun and addictive game which I bought to learn the rules. But the digital version is the one I've played a lot more than the cardboard one.
Don't give up if you're new to this game. I kept getting negative scores as I learned how to play. The rules text is very small too. Finally I scored a 0 and was happy.
Great 1p game!!! I have the physical version of this game and love it! Its a real challenge, and unforgiving.
Being ported to an app gives so much potential, but this is just a lazy porting. No tutorial, no clear interface.

Ich versuch' gerade den Spielstand auf ein anderes Geraet zu uebertragen. E-mail Adresse auf dem alten eingetragen, Bestaetigung mit OTP, so, jetzt muesste mein Spielstand auf euren Servern sein. E-mail Adresse auf dem neuen eingetragen... Fehler, diese E-mail ist schon vergeben... klar ist sie das. Hab ich hier einen Denkfehler, oder funktioniert das auf Eurer Seite nicht richtig?
Excellent#
Great single player experience, but the rules take some getting used to. King of the Island tournaments are great fun!
Amazing solo game. Quick fairly simple rules quite difficult without being impossible. Highly recommended.
Great solo experience. The King of Island tournament is very entertaining.
Great game. You won't need a tutorial if you've played the physical copy before. The interface explains itself, and the only tough part was the game itself, which was already a given.

I wanted to learn this game and thought the app would be a great option. Other board games have great tutorials in their ports. Not here. I should have read the reviews and spared myself the frustrations of a sloppy mobile app.
Love the card game and now I don't need a table! Wasn't clear on how to use some abilities in the app, but the Internet is a 'wonderful' thing.
Excellent solo strategy game and excellent adaptation
When fighting the pirates and lot of cards are on the table, the help text is not shown. Otherwise nice game!
Very clever. Difficult to master
Fantastic solo card game, challenging enough to draw you in time and again. I would have given it 5 stars but the game has trouble connecting and therefore I have never seen the highscore tables.
Takes a bit to learn, little longer to learn a good strategy, but so satisfying once you start having success! Great game
Fantastic digital adaptation of a great solo game.

I don't have experience with the card game outside of the app, so if this is Friedmann's idea I have to say his game bites. But I perfectly build my deck only to be told I've run out of cards, and while my experience should have resulted in a high score I'm eliminated before I get to the pirates with 18 health and no recourse. So while it's an okay game, even an addicting game, it is not a great game.

Very fun game with a biweekly tournament! It also clarifies some of the rules that may be ambiguous on table top. I gave it 4 stars in graphics because some of the menues fade and therefore hover over what you want to see. But not for long, and it's really not that big of a deal. Enjoy!
Love this game. The app is perfect too.
Excellent game.

Good game, poor app. I got this to see if I would like the game. Unfortunately, the app makes playing and understanding the game very difficult, so much so that I've given up and don't even try anymore. E.g.: - no way to see the contents of your deck, the threats deck, discard pile... for a deck building game! - no undo for very basic actions, sometimes costing you the game - activating card powers is really awkward Get Onirim instead. If you wanted to try the game, just buy the physical game.
I bought the boardgame a while ago but this is so much more convenient. This game is so much fun and passes time in a very entertaining way.

Fun if very difficult
Awesome game!! Very like the board game.
Supposedly one of the best one player games, I find it very engaging and still feel far from conquering it as I can see some do in two weekly competition, it will last and last
A great and effective digital translation of a tight and well balanced solo game. Would definitely recommend.
A great implementation of a great game
Pretty great game. However, I'd still prefer the board game to the app due to the HUD.
Frequently fails to allow use of card abilities. Either is bugged or is lacking error messaging as to why.
Needs a tutorial

Good implementation of the board game. It badly needs an info button, though, because the controls are not very intuitive. Also, it frequently crashes when you try and resume a saved game. Best to only play it when you have the time to play it through in one sitting!

- The animations are a bit too slow and nauseating. There's too much spinning, some popups fade very slowly. Turning off animations doesn't really fix this. - It's not possible to go back to the main menu and look at the card reference without ending the game. I can do this by closing the app, but IMO that didn't have to be necessary
Got gud
I can't push the lowest button, because it's not showing all of the screen.

This is based on one of my favorite card games but this app is rough. There are several bugs, some of which are game breaking. I am still using the app but only because I love the game. I hope it is fixed soon so others can enjoy and not hold the lackluster app against a great game. Edit: still no updates.
I. Love. This. Game. üòä
in my top 3 solitaire games

This is a great implementation of the solo board game. Any problems that have popped up have been quickly fixed by developers. An undo button would be nice. 10-2019 there are now ads in this premium game. Before there were sometimes ads for other games by the same developer. I let that pass. The last few days I've gotten ads for what looks like coffee (ad isn't in English). Reported to Google.
This is a great implementation of the card game. Be prepared to loose a lot. üòÇ

Great port of the game. Makes the IRL card game redundant, because you don't have to shuffle cards or keep track of things - the app does that for you. Great for lazy people like me. If you manage to win one of your first 10 games as a newbie player, you are pretty smart. I managed to beat level 5, but that requires a fair bit of luck. I found two problems: higher level games (4-5) are not saved well after quitting the app and I cannot go back to finish them. Also I could not find out how to discard a card with the "Sort 3 cards" ability.

I love the physical game, but this version is just a disgrace. Frequently just stops responding after I choose a hazard card to engage. The whole UI is just embarrassing. It really lacks life. There is no visual or haptic feedback whenever I press things. It's like a badly made website wrapped into an app instead of an app. If you're charging money for it, at least put some effort into it.
Great solo game
Great solo game on the table and now also on my phone
Fun, light game. Challenging at first, gets easier once you get the hang of it.
Great game but real one is better.
good game
Great game but very hard... Also I've noticed a bunch of translation errors
Super awesome, fun, great game. I can't stop playing and don't want to either.
very addictive awesome little game
A great game and a very good implementation.

Great adaptation, a little glitchy. Sometimes taps aren't correctly sensed or applied. This does not really detract too much from gameplay but can be a bit annoying. Over all this is a fun game and moved well from table to screen.
fun and hard and fun again (could do with a tutorial though)

love the card game but there are a fee issues with the app. sometimes using "1 below the stack" seems to break the game and I can keep drawing multiple free cards... also on a couple of occasions the exact same aging card has appeared twice when drawing to fight against a hazard, which shouldn't be possible! also as other people have mentioned there's some typos in the achievement and the game would really benefit from an undo button as it is way to easy to select something by mistake...

The card game this app is based on is an amazing solo experience packed into a small box. Each game has this amazing arc where you're building up your capabilities facing challenges, slowly at first and failing often. Then things ramp up in a very satisfying way and you're just barely hanging on by the skin of your teeth until you finally pull out the win or succumb to the withering onslaught. This app is an excellent port of this very fun and challenging little solo card game.
nice solo game when on the move. Have the boardgame for a long time.

A pretty darn good interpretation of the game. I'll never say an app replaces a game per se, but Friday hits the table a lot less because of this app. That being said the game is definitely easier once you play the physical game as the how to is wholly insufficient. Would be a mark against it but it's a pitch perfect port of one of the best solo board games ever made.
Great game!
Some strange UI design choices.

Instead of a tutorial, it just gives you the game's manual to read. Which would normally be excusable, if it wasn't just a scan of the manual on the LOWEST possible image quality. It is barely legible, even when zoomed all the way in. I can't understand why anyone would think that's okay.
good fun.
No tutorial
It's originally a one player "board" game, but it's better as an app. It's a deck-builder, with the twist that the starting deck is substantially worse than in most games.
Great game but a tutorial would be helpful.
Excellent solo game. Different game every time
cool game
Very good game, really entertaining and good to spend some time.
I've been receiving ads, pretty disappointing since it's a paid app
online doesn't work. and it's the only thing I bought the game for.
Great solo game in a great app. Could use a tutorial.

Features obnoxious pop-up advertisements for their other games, which have no place in a paid app. The gameplay is fun and challenging, a testament to the flawless design of the original board game. However, the tutorial/instructions are near non-existent in the digital version. Many spelling errors; I can guess what "disctracted" was meant to say, but how do i get an "Ear Victory"? It is required for an achievement... ...
throws errors breaking gameplay. poor tutorial
Excellent game, the app is great! No issues. I haven't tried the online part yet.
So hard. You will die
Sounds settings ignored
Great Port of a great solo board game
Great art and gameplay. Actual interface is rather clunky, but that doesn't obscure a great game.
Great implementation of the card game, although I don't know how you'd learn it as there is no tutorial.
So good
My only complaint is I never play my physical copy anymore, so much quicker and easier to play the app.
A charming thoughtful game.
It's a great application. Some of the negative reviews misled me at first. But if u know the rules beforehand and have a bit IQ, u wont have any problem understanding the app or playing it.
Would love an undo option and a better tutorial
Intelligent yet easy game. Highly addictive

Had this game for years. Love it, and now it's on my phone, I play it a lot 
more (and with no rules errors!)

Good implementation of a great solo game. UI can be a little fiddly but 
excellent price point.

I've never played the physical game. There is no tutorial and the 
instructions are in bad 'engrish'. Confusing, but ok, I guess.
Love this game!

It's a fun strategy. Needs better tutorial. I looked up how to play on 
YouTube, I suggest watching Rahdo.
One of my favorite solo game üòä
Nice

Great port of the physical game. I still play the real version whenever I 
can but this version is perfect when I'm stuck on an airplane.
Very hard but interesting
Good but not great app version of the excellent solo game
Good Solo game found out about it on The Dice Tower.

Id give this game 5 stars since it is a great game, but whenever i try 
using the "1x below the stack" it freezes the app. So 1 star until thats 
fixed
I love the board game, and now I can play it on my phone whenever I want!
Just great. Great game, great adaptation and great fun.
Nice adaptation of the card game.
Awesome one player

Love this. It's a fun game, and so challenging. Only thing holding it back 
from five stars would be a better tutorial, or more in-depth rulebook. Had 
to learn card abilities through trial and error, and incorrectly assumed 
food automatically added your health. That said, it's not that hard to 
figure out, and everything else about this app is great.
A solid digital implementation of one of the best solitaire card games.

not much of a tutorial so you have read illegible scan of rulebook. annoying reminders about activations ive alreadt declined. easy to forget what difficulty youre working towards because the only indicator is too subtle. the game itself has some interesting mechanics though and i think if not for the frustrating ui elements and the lack of ability to yndo decisions made because of said ui i dont see myself playing it much
Would be great to have an option of backing out of selecting a card power to play. Sometimes hit a card accidentally but have to continue with mistaken selection because haven't found an out
No option to disable sound? crappy UI? Pop up messages that take 30 seconds to fade? No way to reach settings without quitting your current game?  Total amateur hour developer stay far away folks.
Great implementation of excellent solitaire card game.

I rated this a 4 because the original card game is good. I think this implementation is not. The game gives little to no indication when important events occur. The controls when doubling or swapping cards is inconsistent. It reminds you you have unplayed cards that you wouldn't want to play. This can be so much better.
Great port of the card game

Error preventing game play. Was working when I first installed, but after two plays it no longer functions. Rules assume prior familiarity with the game. Others have made similar comments. After few days, reply from developers came. Suggested I use a beta but not given access. They weren't aware that latest OS is available for my phone, so I'm guessing this could be a widespread issue. May want to contact developers before purchase
Would be good to have a graphic to make it clearer that an ageing card has been added to the deck
Quick and easy to learn. It's a great adaptation of a solo boardgame made for phones.
Tough just like the physical version
Actually a 4.5.  Better than Actual Game as long as you understand the piles.  Sounds and music clips add to the Jungle feel.
Rules illegible on Pixel 2.
Love it!
Good implementation of the card game
The biggest complaint I have on the game is that it doesn't keep track of my high score. I couldn't care less about other people's high score on a single player game.
Closest to the original card game as possible
need tutorial for beginner
Very poor implementation of a really good game. The game itself deserves such a high rating, but the app doesn't

The game itself is very good but the app is horrible! No music, just a few sounds here and there, no tutorial so u need to know the card game, the rulebook is a scan of the card game, hard to read and partly unneeded, animations are very bad, sooo much room for improvement. It looks like an app made by a fan of the game, beginner in app development. And that would be ok IF this was free  ! But it's not !
Excellent adaptation of the card game.
This game sucks. Has zero fun factor

Fun game. Needs immersive mode to hide Android controls and volume controls to adjust very loud sounds. Instructions need to be rewritten (or rescanned) because it took a few videos on YouTube to figure out how to play. There are no ads or in app purchases, which is nice!
Fun
Ack! Can't stop playing! Sooo much  fun....
Good app implementation of clever solo strategy game.
Perfect copy of the card game. Let's me play much more often. Down side? I now rarely use the card game.

Easily the worst professional board game port I've played so far. The games art was never great, but here it looks stretched out. The UI is clunky and uninformative, playing and using card abilities is annoying. There's no tutorial and the rules look like a low quality scan of the rulebook - I'm not sure how anyone who doesn't own the original could learn to play from this app. The title screen isn't even localised! Overall really low quality given the asking price.
Good port of a very good single player board game.

Decent port of my favourite solo card game. The rules are kinda blurry on my Pixel phone (but I own the physical game and remember how to play) but the gameplay is there and level 5 is just as challenging as I remembered.
replyContent: We found the reason for missing translation in certain screens and will release an update later today.

content: Muy bueno

Great game, nice adaptation of the physical card game. I have played probably a couple hundred games by now. Took over 20 games and watching a tutorial video how to play physical game before it clicked for me, but once it did I really enjoyed it. I gave only 4 stars because I agree with many reviews an undo button is sorely needed, many times I have overlooked an ability or my finger was not 100% accurate or I simply realized I made a mistake and there is no way to step back. Developer please add an undo feature!
Really fun little game.
Great game!
Please add an animation when an Aging card is added to the draw deck. It's not always noticed when this happens. Otherwise, an amazing game and digital adaptation!
controls are a bit uncomfortable, but the game is very nice
Pretty good implementation of another great For a Friedmann Friese game....now please bring on Power Grid

It's a good start, but it needs work.   1) There needs to be an undo button.  Several times I have accidentally indicated that I wanted to quit drawing cards and therefore end the round.    The only button available is "OK".  Why even have that if there is no other option? You must be able to keep drawing cards.  2) The main 2 buttons that you use throughout the game (Draw and Stop Drawing) are inconveniently placed in the middle of the screen.  These 2 buttons should be at the bottom of the screen where they can be easily accessed.    I am glad this app is being developed.  It's a cool, strategic game.  I have the card game and this will help me play it more often.  5 stars when these are fixed.
Brilliant version of the card game

Love this. Unfair to rate the graphics as thy are faithful to the game. Controls are not entirely intuitive but make sense once you figure them out. Smooth gameplay an a great implementation.  I would prefer the cards to not change size, and maybe separate t free and bought cards, but otherwise love it.  Really nice app, thank you!!!
Getting better!  Could really use the ability to cancel the fact you clicked on give up the fight.  Too many times I've accidentally hit this button instead of drawing the next card.
replyContent: We found the reason for missing translation in certain screens and will release an update later today.

content: One of my favorite solo card game. Now for phones as well. Perfect!
Plays pretty much like the physical but without shuffling.
Any issues I have had so far were quickly fixed by the developer. This game is great, I own the physical version as well. This is by far one of my favorite solo board games.
replyContent:
Hi Cory,

do you get an error message? We fixed a problem where the message is not in english, hopefully this will help you. The update will be live in aboutr an hour!

content: Worked fine until the last update. Since then, the app crashes after defeating the first pirate :(
Two times in a row, when I defeated the first pirate, the game crashed. It is pretty frustrating putting time into a game you cannot win

The app is a mess. There are still parts that are in German (in the English "translation)". The rules are too small to read in a phone and to blurry to read on a tablet. There is no tutorial. If you know the game well you might enjoy the app. If you don't know the game, avoid this app.
Great game, good implementation but lacks a tutorial.  Also throws an incomprehensible error message when "Copy" is used incorrectly.
Exactly like the physical edition, one of my fav time killers at boardgame night now more portable
Game is not finished. If you don't already know how to play, don't buy.
replyContent:
Hi Bill,

we fixed the missing translations in certain screens and will release an update later today.
If you have any other issues please elaborate, so we can make it better!

content: Good implementation, but score breakdown and options (maybe others) are in German even though I have the game in English.
